# Mongoose Models

```typescript
const schema = new Schema({ ... }, { timestamps: true, collection: "grammar_today" });
const Model = models?.grammarToday || model("grammarToday", schema, "grammar_today");
```

- Collection names: snake_case
- Always use `models?.name || model(...)` for hot-reload safety
- Prefer aggregation (`$match`, `$sample`, `$group`) in API routes like existing code
- Connection only via `connectDB` — never open a second mongoose connection in models
